For n \geqslant p, we have W_n( \Omega _X^p \langle Y \rangle ) = \Omega _X^p \langle Y \rangle and so \alpha is a morphism from \Omega _X^ \bullet \langle Y \rangle, endowed with \tau, to \Omega _X^ \bullet \langle Y \rangle, endowed with the decreasing filtration associated to W (). By [hodge-theory-ii-3.1.5.2 (?)], we have
